<TITLE> Lift emergency, ensure right environment: Bhuiyan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 7 (bdnews24.com)  Former BNP secretary general Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan on Friday demanded withdrawal of the state of emergency and an atmosphere conducive for general election. He would run in the upcoming election, he told a rally of his supporters at Labpur under Dulalpur union of Shibpur upazila in his home constituency of Narsingdi Friday. He came to Shibpur from Dhaka in the morning to do public relations and returned to Dhaka in the evening. Aiming at the government, Bhuiyan said, "We want a neutral and fair electoral environment. The government would have to do everything necessary to ensure that." "Now I do not have any party or symbol. People of Shibpur are my address. I will take part in the election for their sake." Bhuiyan also demanded introduction of agricultural loan and rationing. Shibpur BNP convenor Abul Haris Rikabdar, member secretary Ariful Islam Mridha, leaders and workers of pro- BNP Jatiyatabadi Jubo Dal, Chhatra Dal and other associate organisations were present. bdne
